A Caisson is used in [[Civil Engineering]] to hold back water during [[construction]]. It is normally a manmade [[Dam]] that completely surronds the work site.


In [[Dockyard]]s, Caissons are used as floating gates to hold back the water in [[Drydock]]. 

Pronounced Case-on, although it is often mis-pronounced as Ka - soon.

